      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is the most objective framework because it anchors legal interpretation in verifiable historical fact, unlike subjective approaches. While the world has changed, the fundamental principles enshrined in the Constitution are meant to be enduring, not subject to transient social trends. Other frameworks, like living constitutionalism, are inherently subjective, allowing judges to inject their contemporary political views into the law. Therefore, originalism provides the only truly stable and defensible standard for constitutional law.",
      "source": "target",
